a:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1140" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/469bc180-c72a-11ed-b7fa-c5717b49db91" width="1901"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Amazon]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A white Amazon Echo Show 8 displays the time and temperature while resting on a side table in front of a potted plant and cup of coffee, next to a white couch.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Amazon Echo Show 8 (2nd gen)]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Morning After: The games industry is massive, so why is it shrinking?]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>昨天标志着<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/summer-game-fest-2023-and-the-stagnant-state-of-the-industry-163019962.html">夏季游戏节</a></ins>，一个填补被取消的 E3 留下的空白的事件。这是游戏行业的盛会，开发商和发行商可以为他们目前正在开发的游戏大肆宣传。但是，尽管业务从未像现在这样更大或更有利可图，但人们也感觉到博彩业正在萎缩。</p><p>这在很大程度上是因为两个最大的玩家，微软和索尼，正在竭尽全力巩固他们的权力和影响力。两家公司都已经购买并正在尝试购买主要的独立发行商和工作室，以加强自己的生态系统。这两个巨头都有可能拉起他们的吊桥，进一步分裂一个已经容易破裂的行业。</p><p>但这不是唯一的问题，出版商迫使成功的开发者开发他们没有经验的游戏。最近的例子是<em>Redfall</em> ，据报道，它是由一家发行商创建的，该发行商希望提高其在线多人游戏的盈利能力。然后，这个头衔被交给了一支以精心打造的单人游戏体验而闻名的团队，并被告知继续前进，导致了一场备受批评的失败。</p><p>但这只是游戏行业面临的众多问题之一<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/summer-game-fest-2023-and-the-stagnant-state-of-the-industry-163019962.html">杰西卡·康迪特 (Jessica Conditt) 的国情咨文故事引领夏季运动会盛宴</a></ins>.如果您想知道为什么感觉有很多可能性，但现在却很少，那么值得一试。</p><p> – 丹·库珀</p><p><em>The Morning After 不仅仅是一份</em><a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/about/newsletter/"><em>时事通讯</em></a><em>——它还是一个每日播客。</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-08-01-engadget-podcasts.html"><em>在这里订阅</em></a><em>，获取周一至周五的每日音频简报</em><em>。</em></p><p></p><h3>你可能错过的最重要的故事</h3><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-photography-gifts-for-dads-135953254.html">给爸爸最好的摄影礼物</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/john-carpenters-toxic-commando-brings-a-co-op-apocalypse-to-ps5-and-xbox-203721417.html">“John Carpenter&#39;s Toxic Commando”为 PS5、PC 和 Xbox 带来了合作世界末日</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/whatsapps-new-channels-feature-lets-accounts-send-one-way-updates-to-followers-090843232.html">WhatsApp 的新频道功能可让帐户向关注者发送单向更新</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nest-wifi-pro-routers-are-down-to-record-low-prices-in-a-google-smart-home-sale-171544829.html">Nest WiFi Pro 路由器在谷歌智能家居销售中创历史新低</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-meet-makes-the-picture-in-picture-experience-far-more-useful-133711144.html">Google Meet 让画中画体验更有用</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-password-manager-gets-new-security-and-usability-features-035347775.html">Google 密码管理器获得新的安全性和可用性功能</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-for-ios-gets-support-for-siri-and-shortcuts-095557134.html">iOS 版 ChatGPT 获得对 Siri 和快捷方式的支持</a></ins></p><p><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alan-wake-ii-gameplay-shows-newcomer-saga-battling-a-resurrected-murder-victim-202108350.html">“Alan Wake II”游戏玩法显示新人 Saga 与复活的谋杀受害者作斗争</a></ins></p><p></p><h2><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/united-is-putting-4k-displays-and-bluetooth-on-its-planes-103520707.html">美联航正在其飞机上安装 4K 显示器和蓝牙</a></ins></h2><h3>现在，让这些飞机准时运行。</h3><figure> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/united-is-putting-4k-displays-and-bluetooth-on-its-planes-103520707.html"><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/b5d6a2d0-06af-11ee-bfff-226c969af226" style="height:427px;width:675px;" alt="联合航空公司的新 4K IFE 图像显示在一排飞机座位上。" data-uuid="2ee44836-b53d-328a-a119-d98285b14bd4"></a><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/united-is-putting-4k-displays-and-bluetooth-on-its-planes-103520707.html">松下航空电子公司</a></div></figure><p>美国联合航空公司宣布将为其机队购买 300,000 个最先进的机上娱乐设备。 Panasonic Avionics 制造的装置将有 10 英寸（经济）或 13 英寸（第一）<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/united-is-putting-4k-displays-and-bluetooth-on-its-planes-103520707.html">内置蓝牙的 4K OLED 屏幕</a></ins>.遗憾的是，屏幕的推出要到 2025 年才会开始，而且它仅适用于国际舰队，至少目前是这样。</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/united-is-putting-4k-displays-and-bluetooth-on-its-planes-103520707.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></ins></p><h2><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/third-party-reddit-app-apollo-will-shut-down-on-june-30th-174305150.html">第三方 Reddit 应用 Apollo 将于 6 月 30 日关闭</a></ins></h2><h3><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/reddit-ceo-will-host-an-ama-on-api-changes-as-thousands-of-subreddits-plan-to-go-dark-193423226.html">Reddit CEO 将主持关于 API 更改的 AMA，因为成千上万的 subreddits 计划“变黑”</a></ins></h3><figure> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/third-party-reddit-app-apollo-will-shut-down-on-june-30th-174305150.html"><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/fe6269d0-06af-11ee-bcef-c55cfd674fff" style="height:416px;width:625px;" alt="iPhone 上的 Reddit 标志" data-uuid="8cdbf295-dd01-31dc-8901-dc609bd49a6a"></a><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/third-party-reddit-app-apollo-will-shut-down-on-june-30th-174305150.html">LIONEL BONAVENTURE 来自 Getty Images</a></div></figure><p> Reddit 最近宣布改变其 API 定价，对第三方应用程序开发人员产生巨大影响。受欢迎的 Reddit 客户端 Apollo 表示，这些变化意味着它每年向 Reddit 支付 2000 万美元，只是为了维持其现有服务——领先的创建者 Christian Selig 宣布该应用程序将<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/third-party-reddit-app-apollo-will-shut-down-on-june-30th-174305150.html">6月30日关闭</a></ins>.</p><p>此举让 Reddit 用户陷入混乱，超过 3,000 个知名子版块计划“关闭”48 小时以示抗议。 Reddit 首席执行官史蒂夫霍夫曼随后宣布他将<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/reddit-ceo-will-host-an-ama-on-api-changes-as-thousands-of-subreddits-plan-to-go-dark-193423226.html">解决网站庞大的社区</a></ins>在 6 月 9 日星期五的 Ask Me Anything (AMA) 中。不过，有趣的是，该事件的简洁公告忽略了对那些可能注定失败的第三方客户的后果。</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/third-party-reddit-app-apollo-will-shut-down-on-june-30th-174305150.html"><strong>继续阅读（阿波罗）</strong></a></ins></p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/reddit-ceo-will-host-an-ama-on-api-changes-as-thousands-of-subreddits-plan-to-go-dark-193423226.html"><strong>继续阅读（霍夫曼）</strong></a></ins></p><h2><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonic-superstars-gives-classic-gameplay-another-modern-makeover-200643371.html">“Sonic Superstars”为经典游戏玩法带来了另一种现代改造</a></ins></h2><h3>今年秋天它几乎无处不在。</h3><figure> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/sonic-superstars-gives-classic-gameplay-another-modern-makeover-200643371.html"><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/42db67b0-06b0-11ee-bfde-fae24a0857d4" style="height:351px;width:625px;" alt="Sonic Superstars 的屏幕截图显示 Sonic 在重新制作的 Green Hill Zone 中滚下陡峭的斜坡。" data-uuid="3a3cad61-3fe0-370b-9008-da17dc4c0076"></a><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/sonic-superstars-gives-classic-gameplay-another-modern-makeover-200643371.html">世嘉</a></div></figure><p>现在，我老了，愤世嫉俗，厌倦了，但确实感觉每隔两年左右，我们就会有一款“回归本源”的刺猬索尼克游戏。你知道，一个自豪地宣布该系列的人将回归其作为横向卷轴动作平台游戏的根源，并具有现代风格。 <em>Sonic Superstars</em>是最新的，<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonic-superstars-gives-classic-gameplay-another-modern-makeover-200643371.html">承诺回归横向卷轴动作</a></ins>，尽管具有更现代的图形和合作游戏。不幸的是，我也正处于全力投入尝试的地步，希望能重新点燃我儿时对 Sega 的 Blue Blur 的热爱。</p><p> （好吧，我看了看， <em>Sonic Mania</em>是 2017 年， <em>Sonic 4</em>是 2012 年，所以它更像是一个<em>五年</em>周期。）</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonic-superstars-gives-classic-gameplay-another-modern-makeover-200643371.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></ins></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spider-man-2-launches-on-october-20th-203245436.html">《蜘蛛侠 2》将于 10 月 20 日上映</a></ins></h2><h3>这是 PS5 独占。</h3><figure> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/spider-man-2-launches-on-october-20th-203245436.html"><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/77739ba0-06b0-11ee-beff-b9023bced62b" style="height:351px;width:625px;" alt="PS5 版“蜘蛛侠 2”的宣传图片" data-uuid="6eb3c11e-b5d4-3350-8afb-5f39fec1a965"></a><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"><a href="https://www.engadget.com/spider-man-2-launches-on-october-20th-203245436.html">漫威 / 索尼 / Insomniac</a></div></figure><p>万众期待的<em>蜘蛛侠2</em>将于10月20日发售，6月16日PS5独占开启预购。在里面，<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spider-man-2-launches-on-october-20th-203245436.html">彼得帕克将与迈尔斯莫拉莱斯合作</a></ins>, 你可以在两个角色之间即时切换。 Insomniac Games 的 James Stevenson 补充说，两位主角都有自己特定的故事情节和任务等你完成。虽然考虑到帕克和莫拉莱斯并列榜首，但这款游戏肯定应该被称为<em>2 Spider-Man</em>或<em>Spider-Men</em>或<em>2 Spiders 2 Men，</em>对吧？</p><p><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spider-man-2-launches-on-october-20th-203245436.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></ins></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-the-games-industry-is-massive-so-why-is-it-shrinking-111503778.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-the-games-industry-is-massive-so-why-is-it-shrinking-111503778.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 294960db-8452-425f-b058-08d4a49a1b20</guid><dc:creator>丹尼尔·库珀</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 09 Jun 2023 11:15:03 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686306970</ingested><modified> 2023-06-09T10:36:22+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="4584" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/56310280-06af-11ee-b8ef-bd02fd641c7d" width="8149"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4584" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/56310280-06af-11ee-b8ef-bd02fd641c7d" width="8149"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Future Publishing via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Living room with Microsoft Xbox Series X (L) and Sony PlayStation 5 home video game consoles alongside a television and soundbar, taken on November 3, 2020. (Photo by Phil Barker/Future Publishing via Getty Images via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Xbox Series X & PlayStation 5]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mercedes becomes the first automaker to sell Level 3 self-driving vehicles in California]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/1-california-dmv-conditionally-approves-175205411.html"><em>据路透社</em></a>报道，梅赛德斯-奔驰是第一家获得加州监管机构许可的汽车制造商，可以在指定道路上销售或租赁配备 3 级（免提和免视）自动驾驶技术的车辆。加州机动车辆管理局为该公司的 Drive Pilot 系统颁发了许可证，前提是该系统必须在特定条件下和特定道路上使用。梅赛德斯-奔驰此前在内华达州也获得了<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-first-certified-level-3-autonomy-car-company-us-201021118.html">类似的认证</a>。</p><p> Drive Pilot 将允许梅赛德斯-奔驰司机将视线从道路上移开，双手从方向盘上移开，然后进行其他非驾驶活动，如观看视频和发短信。如果遵守使用规则，梅赛德斯（而非驾驶员）将对发生的任何事故承担法律责任。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="1a7b9ff6895241f6aa92d7835bdf06d0"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5TWKFHsvseo?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen scrolling="no"></iframe></div></div><p>为此，Drive Pilot 系统依靠安装在整个车辆上的传感器，包括视觉摄像头、LiDAR 阵列、雷达/超声波传感器和音频麦克风，以留意接近的紧急车辆。它甚至可以比较车载传感器和 GPS 数据，以确定其在道路上的精确位置。</p><p>它不像<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/waymo-brings-its-fleet-of-new-self-driving-suvs-to-austin-165720284.html">Waymo</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cruise-robotaxi-1-million-driverless-miles-170051724.html">Cruise</a>车辆上的系统那么先进，后者允许在无人驾驶的情况下实现全自动驾驶。同时，它比特斯拉所谓的全自动驾驶系统更进一步，该系统实际上是 2 级系统，要求驾驶员始终将手放在方向盘上并保持注意力。</p><p>使用仅限于白天交通繁忙的情况，速度低于 40 MPH，并且必须有司机才能恢复控制——例如，这样你就不能坐在后座上睡觉。为了强制执行这一点，车辆使用车载监视器跟踪驾驶员，如果速度超过 40MPH、紧急车辆出现、下雨或其他 Driver Pilot 无法处理的情况，您需要接管它自己的。</p><p>该系统将用于 2024 S 级和 EQS 轿车车型，预计于今年晚些时候交付。 Engadget 能够在德国梅赛德斯-奔驰的测试跑道上<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:YouTube;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=89f68c82-f255-44fa-8db9-03fec996b93a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=YouTube&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4OWY2OGM4Mi1mMjU1LTQ0ZmEtOGRiOS0wM2ZlYzk5NmI5M2EiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj01VFdLRkhzdnNlbyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNGZjNDI5NWEtMWRiOS00ZDIyLWFmZWEtNWIwMzkwMjE2ZGMyIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAT1jZkBkViVWQr5tjkZ71p5e4WceXLyYHkVH_EzfhP7M&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D5TWKFHsvseo" class="rapid-with-clickid">测试该系统</a>（并在洛杉矶的道路上<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:YouTube;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=89f68c82-f255-44fa-8db9-03fec996b93a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=YouTube&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4OWY2OGM4Mi1mMjU1LTQ0ZmEtOGRiOS0wM2ZlYzk5NmI5M2EiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1zTU5uT29zanJCbyZ0PTIzN3MiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjRmYzQyOTVhLTFkYjktNGQyMi1hZmVhLTViMDM5MDIxNmRjMiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASwR45rTgDR16TLyT5odqC8n8dXbjo3J1AuGIupUEYaa&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DsMNnOosjrBo%26t%3D237s" class="rapid-with-clickid">看到它的运行情况</a>）。 <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-drive-pilot-level-3-autonomous-video-220158620.html">根据</a>撰稿人罗伯托鲍德温的说法，“虽然它做了它应该做的事情，但我们发现很难在驾驶时关闭我们的驾驶大脑。”</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-becomes-the-first-automaker-to-sell-level-3-self-driving-vehicles-in-california-103504319.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/mercedes-becomes-the-first-automaker-to-sell-level-3-self-driving-vehicles-in-california-103504319.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4fc4295a-1db9-4d22-afea-5b0390216dc2</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 09 Jun 2023 10:35:04 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686306806</ingested><modified> 2023-06-09T10:33:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Automotive Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|