3571.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-desantis-campaign-used-ai-generated-images-to-attack-trump-062923571.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 238e383f-1f24-44fc-b713-ac8bd1fe56ba</guid><dc:creator>玛丽拉月亮</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 09 Jun 2023 06:29:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686292165</ingested><modified> 2023-06-09T06:29:29+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="2946" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/903d24c0-0684-11ee-aebb-b8e5b35945fa" width="4200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2946" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/903d24c0-0684-11ee-aebb-b8e5b35945fa" width="4200"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Anadolu Agency via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[WILDWOOD, FLORIDA, UNITED STATES - JUNE 6: Republican presidential candidate Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis speaks during a press conference during which he signed a bill to protect the digital rights of Floridians, on June 6, 2023 in Wildwood, Florida. (Photo by Paul Hennessy/Anadolu Agency via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Florida Gov. DeSantis Signs Digital Bill of Rights]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[GM EV owners will gain access to Tesla Superchargers in 2024]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ford-ev-drivers-will-get-access-to-12000-north-american-tesla-superchargers-next-spring-221752191.html">福特并不是唯一一家转向特斯拉北美充电标准的电动汽车制造商</a>——通用汽车表示它也在做出改变。首席执行官玛丽巴拉周四在与特斯拉首席执行官埃隆马斯克的 Twitter Spaces 聊天中宣布了这一举措，并表示其电动汽车将在 2025 年在所有通用汽车电动汽车中采用 NACS 开源连接器标准。</p><p>作为合作的一部分，所有通用汽车电动汽车将在 2024 年获得 12,000 个特斯拉增压器。现有通用汽车电动汽车的驾驶员无需升级他们的车辆即可使用特斯拉的充电器，但需要使用适配器使他们的车辆兼容。同样，通用汽车表示将开发一种适配器，允许未来支持 NACS 的电动汽车为其现有的支持 CSS 的快速充电站网络充电。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>向后兼容的充电器可能很重要。特斯拉最初宣布愿意向非特斯拉汽车开放其充电系统，同时宣布了一项<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-reportedly-trying-to-offer-prime-subscribers-free-cell-phone-service-140026387.html">75 亿美元的拜登政府计划</a>，旨在扩大美国电动汽车充电器的可用性——但该计划在很大程度上建立了 CCS 充电器。</p><p> “这次合作是我们战略的关键部分，也是为我们的客户迅速扩大快速充电器接入的重要下一步，”巴拉在通用汽车关于合作伙伴关系的声明中表示。 “我们对全电动未来的愿景意味着生产数百万辆跨类别和价位的世界级电动汽车，同时创建一个生态系统，以加速大规模采用电动汽车。”</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/gm-ev-owners-will-gain-access-to-tesla-superchargers-in-2024-002123436.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/gm-ev-owners-will-gain-access-to-tesla-superchargers-in-2024-002123436.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9258b70b-f2f5-4ff5-9736-91eee16b893e</guid><dc:creator>肖恩·巴克利</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 09 Jun 2023 00:21:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686270079</ingested><modified> 2023-06-09T00:21:23+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Automotive Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Renewable Energy & Energy Saving]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><cate